M|Lean|tx|A systematic approach to building startups and launching new pd that shortens dv cycles and rapidly discovers if a business md is viable.
M|Core|tx|**Entrepreneurship is a form of management.** sc doesn't require a perfect plan or brilliant in—it requires a systematic process for testing assumptions, learning from cs, and iterating rapidly.
M|Core|**Th|** Most startups fail not bc they couldn't bd what they planned, but bc they built the wrong thing. The Lean Startup methodology applies scientific experimentation to eliminate waste and accelerate validated learning.
M|Scor|**Go|10/10.** When reviewing or creating pd dv plans, experiments, or metrics, rate them 0-10 based on adherence to Lean Startup principles. A 10/10 means full application of bd-Measure-Learn, validated learning, and evidence-based decisions; lower scores indicate waterfall thinking or waste. Always provide the current score and specific improvements needed to reach 10/10.
M|The |The |
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|IDEAS
M|The |tx|↓
M|The |tx|bd → pd
M|The |tx|↓
M|The |tx|MEASURE → Data
M|The |tx|↓
M|The |tx|LEARN → Knowledge
M|The |tx|↓
M|The |tx|(back to IDEAS)
M|The |tx|```
M|The |**Cr|** The loop is actually backward. Start w/ what you want to learn, determine metrics that will inform that learning, then bd the minimum pd to collect those metrics.
M|The |**Re|**
M|The |tx|1. **What do we want to learn?** (hypothesis to tst)
M|The |tx|2. **How will we know if we learned it?** (metrics)
M|The |tx|3. **What's the minimum we can bd?** (MVP)
M|The |**Go|** Minimize total time through the loop.
M|The |See|[references/bd-measure-learn.md](references/bd-measure-learn.md) for detailed loop execution.
M|Vali|**De|** Learning what cs really want through validated experiments, not opinion or anecdotes.
M|Vali|**Va|**
M|Vali|it|Building features cs request (they don't know what they want)
M|Vali|it|Achieving vanity metrics (downloads, signups w/o engagement)
M|Vali|it|Doing surveys or focus groups (people lie/mispredict behavior)
M|Vali|**Va|**
M|Vali|it|Testing hypotheses w/ real behavior
M|Vali|it|Measuring what cs *do*, not what they *say*
M|Vali|it|Running experiments that cld falsify your assumptions
M|Vali|it|Learning = when your predictions were wrong
M|Vali|**Th|**
M|Vali|tx|\| Level \| Evidence \| Strength \|
M|Vali|tx|\|-------\|----------\|----------\|
M|Vali|tx|\| 1 \| "I think cs want this" \| Weakest (opinion) \|
M|Vali|tx|\| 2 \| "cs said they want this" \| Weak (stated preference) \|
M|Vali|tx|\| 3 \| "cs signed up for early access" \| md (lo commitment) \|
M|Vali|tx|\| 4 \| "cs paid a deposit" \| Strong (real commitment) \|
M|Vali|tx|\| 5 \| "cs are actively using it" \| Strongest (revealed preference) \|
M|Vali|**Ta|** Level 4-5 before building at scale.
M|Mini|**De|** The version of a new pd that allows a team to collect the maximum amount of validated learning w/ the least effort.
M|Mini|**MV|**
M|Mini|it|A prototype (not abt proving tc feasibility)
M|Mini|it|A beta version (not abt qual or features)
M|Mini|it|A minimum marketable pd (it might be embarrassing)
M|Mini|**MV|**
M|Mini|it|A learning vehicle
M|Mini|it|The smallest experiment to tst a hypothesis
M|Mini|it|Often much smaller than you think
M|Mini|**MV|**
M|Mini|tx|\| tp \| What It Is \| When to Use \| Example \|
M|Mini|tx|\|------\|------------\|-------------\|---------\|
M|Mini|tx|\| **Concierge** \| Manual service pretending to be automated \| tst if solution is valuable \| Food on the Table (manual meal planning) \|
M|Mini|tx|\| **Wizard of Oz** \| Fake automation, manual backend \| tst if automation is needed \| Zappos (no inventory, bought shoes retail) \|
M|Mini|tx|\| **Smoke tst** \| Landing page + signup, no pd \| tst demand before building \| Dropbox vd (explained concept, measured signups) \|
M|Mini|tx|\| **Single feature** \| One core feature only \| tst which feature is most valuable \| Twitter (just status updates) \|
M|Mini|tx|\| **Piecemeal** \| Combine existing tools \| tst workflow before custom bd \| Groupon (WordPress + em) \|
M|Mini|**MV|**
M|Mini|it|What's the riskiest assumption to tst first?
M|Mini|it|What's the minimum to tst that assumption?
M|Mini|it|How do we measure if the assumption was validated?
M|Mini|**Co|**
M|Mini|it|Building too much (overestimate MVP size)
M|Mini|it|Optimizing for scale prematurely
M|Mini|it|Confusing qual w/ learning (MVP can be lo qual)
M|Mini|it|Skipping the experiment (building w/o hypothesis)
M|Mini|See|[references/mvp-ds.md](references/mvp-ds.md) for MVP tp and ds patterns.
M|Leap|**De|** The assumptions that, if wrong, will cause your business to fail.
M|Leap|**Pr|**
M|Leap|tx|1. **Identify your business md's ct assumptions**
M|Leap|tx|2. **Prioritize by risk** (which fl wld be fatal?)
M|Leap|tx|3. **tst the riskiest assumption first**
M|Leap|**Co|**
M|Leap|tx|\| Assumption tp \| Question \| tst Method \|
M|Leap|tx|\|----------------\|----------\|-------------\|
M|Leap|tx|\| **Value hypothesis** \| Do cs care abt this problem? \| Smoke tst, concierge MVP \|
M|Leap|tx|\| **Growth hypothesis** \| How will cs discover us? \| Channel tests, referral experiments \|
M|Leap|tx|\| **Retention hypothesis** \| Will cs come back? \| Cohort al, engagement metrics \|
M|Leap|tx|\| **Monetization hypothesis** \| Will cs pay? \| Pre-orders, pricing tests \|
M|Leap|**Ex|Dropbox**
M|Leap|- **|** "People will download and use a file sync tool"
M|Leap|- **|** Explainer vd showing pd (before building full version)
M|Leap|- **|** Beta signup list grew from 5,000 to 75,000 overnight
M|Leap|- **|** Validated demand before building scale infrastructure
M|Leap|**An|** Testing assumptions in order of ease rather than risk.
M|Leap|See|[references/assumptions.md](references/assumptions.md) for assumption mapping frameworks.
M|Inno|**De|** Measuring progress when traditional accounting doesn't apply.
M|Inno|**Th|**
M|Inno|it|rv (startups start at $0)
M|Inno|it|cs (startups start at 0)
M|Inno|it|Vanity metrics (look good but don't drive decisions)
M|Inno|**In|**
M|1. E|**Qu|** Where are we today?
M|1. E|tx|Measure current reality, even if it's zero or embarrassing.
M|1. E|**Me|**
M|1. E|it|Conversion funnel (signup → active → retained → paying)
M|1. E|it|Engagement (DAU/MAU, sn length, features used)
M|1. E|it|Economics (CAC, LTV, churn rate)
M|1. E|**Go|** Know your starting point precisely.
M|2. T|**Qu|** What can we improve to move toward our goal?
M|2. T|tx|Run experiments to improve baseline metrics.
M|2. T|**Ex|**
M|2. T|it|A/B tst pricing ($9/mo vs. $19/mo)
M|2. T|it|tst onboarding flows (% who complete setup)
M|2. T|it|Experiment w/ channels (SEO vs. paid vs. referral)
M|2. T|**Go|** Systematically improve metrics through validated learning.
M|3. P|**Qu|** Are we making sufficient progress, or do we need to change st?
M|3. P|tx|Based on data, decide whether to continue or pivot.
M|3. P|**Cr|**
M|3. P|it|Are metrics moving in the right direction?
M|3. P|it|Is the rate of improvement acceptable?
M|3. P|it|Are we learning what we expected?
M|3. P|**Go|** Make evidence-based st decisions.
M|3. P|See|[references/innovation-accounting.md](references/innovation-accounting.md) for metric frameworks and dashboards.
M|Acti|**Va|** Make you feel good but don't change behavior.
M|Acti|**Ac|** Drive decisions and clarify cause and effect.
M|Acti|tx|\| Vanity \| Why It's Bad \| Actionable Alternative \|
M|Acti|tx|\|--------\|-------------\|------------------------\|
M|Acti|tx|\| **Total signups** \| Always goes up, no context \| **% signup → active** (conversion rate) \|
M|Acti|tx|\| **Page views** \| Doesn't indicate value \| **Time on page**, **bounce rate** \|
M|Acti|tx|\| **Total us** \| Includes inactive/churned \| **Active us** (DAU, WAU, MAU) \|
M|Acti|tx|\| **Downloads** \| Doesn't mean usage \| **DAU/downloads** (activation rate) \|
M|Acti|tx|\| **rv** \| w/o context \| **rv per cohort**, **LTV/CAC** \|
M|Acti|**Th|**
M|Acti|1. *|** Clear cause-and-effect (can reproduce)
M|Acti|2. *|** Simple, understandable by everyone
M|Acti|3. *|** Can check the underlying data (not a black box)
M|Acti|**Ex|**
M|Acti|- **|** "We have 100,000 us!"
M|Acti|- **|** "us from channel X have 2x retention vs. channel Y. Let's double down on X."
M|Acti|**Co|** Group us by signup date and track behavior over time. Reveals if pd is actually improving.
M|Acti|See|[references/metrics.md](references/metrics.md) for metric selection and tracking.
M|Pivo|**Pi|** A structured course correction designed to tst a new hypothesis abt the pd, st, or engine of growth.
M|Pivo|**Wh|**
M|Pivo|it|Experiments consistently fail to validate hypotheses
M|Pivo|it|Metrics are flat despite multiple iterations
M|Pivo|it|cs feedback contradicts your vision
M|Pivo|it|Progress is too slow given runway
M|Pivo|**Wh|**
M|Pivo|it|Metrics are improving (even if slowly)
M|Pivo|it|Clear learning is happening
M|Pivo|it|Adjustments are moving in right direction
M|Pivo|**Pi|**
M|Pivo|tx|\| Pivot tp \| What Changes \| Example \|
M|Pivo|tx|\|------------\|-------------\|---------\|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Zoom-in pivot** \| Single feature becomes the whole pd \| Instagram (photo filters from Burbn check-in app) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Zoom-out pivot** \| pd becomes a single feature \| Flickr (photo-sharing from Game Neverending) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **cs segment** \| Same problem, different cs \| Groupon (activism platform → local deals) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **cs need** \| Same cs, different problem \| Potbelly Sandwich (antique store → sandwiches) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Platform** \| App → Platform or Platform → App \| YouTube (dating site → vd platform) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Business architecture** \| hi margin, lo volume ↔ lo margin, hi volume \| Salesforce (software → SaaS) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Value capture** \| Monetization md change \| Android (paid → free + app rv) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Engine of growth** \| Viral, sticky, or paid growth md \| Facebook (viral within colleges → paid advertising) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Channel** \| How you reach cs \| Salesforce (direct sales → self-service) \|
M|Pivo|tx|\| **Technology** \| Different technology, same solution \| Apple (Intel → ARM chips) \|
M|Pivo|**Pi|** Many successful startups pivot 1-5 times before finding pd-mk fit.
M|Pivo|**An|** "Pivot" w/o validating that the new direction solves the core problem.
M|Pivo|See|[references/pivots.md](references/pivots.md) for pivot decision frameworks and case studies.
M|The |**Gr|** How your startup acquires and retains cs sustainably.
M|The |**Ch|**
M|1. S|**Me|** hi retention, lo churn
M|1. S|**Fo|** `Growth rate = New cs acquisition rate - Churn rate`
M|1. S|**Fo|** Keep cs coming back
M|1. S|**Me|**
M|1. S|it|Churn rate (% who stop using per month)
M|1. S|it|Retention cohorts (% still active after 30/60/90 days)
M|1. S|it|Engagement (DAU/MAU ratio)
M|1. S|**Ex|** SaaS, subscription services, sl networks
M|1. S|st|** Improve pd until churn rate is lo enough that natural growth exceeds churn.
M|2. V|**Me|** cs bring other cs
M|2. V|**Fo|** `Viral coefficient = (% who invite) × (invites sent) × (% who join)`
M|2. V|**Fo|** Viral coefficient > 1.0 = exponential growth
M|2. V|**Me|**
M|2. V|it|Viral coefficient (invites → signups)
M|2. V|it|Viral cycle time (how long until referred us invites others)
M|2. V|it|Referral source attribution
M|2. V|**Ex|** Dropbox, Hotmail, WhatsApp
M|2. V|st|** bd virality into the pd. Must be > 1.0 to be self-sustaining.
M|3. P|**Me|** Spend money to acquire cs
M|3. P|**Fo|** `LTV (Lifetime Value) > CAC (cs Acquisition Cost)`
M|3. P|**Fo|** Unit economics that allow reinvestment
M|3. P|**Me|**
M|3. P|it|CAC (cost per acquisition)
M|3. P|it|LTV (average rv per cs)
M|3. P|- LT|> 3x)
M|3. P|it|Payback period (how long to recoup CAC)
M|3. P|**Ex|** E-commerce, traditional businesses
M|3. P|st|** op until each cs generates enough profit to acquire more cs.
M|3. P|wn|** Don't use multiple engines simultaneously. Pick one, op it, then consider adding others.
M|3. P|See|[references/growth-engines.md](references/growth-engines.md) for engine selection and op.
M|The |**Pu|** Root cause al to prevent problems from recurring.
M|The |**Pr|**
M|The |tx|1. A problem occurs (bug, outage, cs complaint)
M|The |tx|2. Ask "Why did this happen?" → Answer
M|The |tx|3. Ask "Why?" abt that answer → Second answer
M|The |tx|4. Repeat 5 times until you reach the root cause
M|The |tx|5. Make proportional investments at each level
M|The |**Ex|**
M|The |**Pr|** Website went down
M|The |tx|1. **Why?** Server ran out of memory
M|The |tx|2. **Why?** Memory leak in new feature
M|The |tx|3. **Why?** Code wasn't reviewed for memory management
M|The |tx|4. **Why?** No code rv process for infrastructure changes
M|The |tx|5. **Why?** Team is moving too fast to cr processes
M|The |**Pr|**
M|The |it|Fix the immediate bug (level 1)
M|The |it|Add memory monitoring (level 2)
M|The |it|im code rv (level 3-4)
M|The |it|Slow down to bd qual processes (level 5)
M|The |**An|** Stop at level 1 (just fix the symptom).
M|The |See|[references/five-whys.md](references/five-whys.md) for facilitation guides.
M|Smal|**Pr|** Work in small batches to accelerate learning and reduce waste.
M|Smal|**Wh|**
M|Smal|it|Faster feedback loops
M|Smal|it|Easier to pivot
M|Smal|it|Less waste when you're wrong
M|Smal|it|Faster time to mk
M|Smal|**Ex|**
M|Smal|tx|\| Large Batch \| Small Batch \|
M|Smal|tx|\|-------------\|-------------\|
M|Smal|tx|\| bd entire pd, then launch \| Launch landing page, then bd \|
M|Smal|tx|\| Release quarterly \| Release weekly or daily \|
M|Smal|tx|\| Plan 12-month roadmap \| Plan 6-week cycles \|
M|Smal|tx|\| Big bang rewrite \| Incremental refactoring \|
M|Smal|**Co|** The ultimate small batch = dp every code commit.
M|Smal|**Be|**
M|Smal|it|Bugs are caught immediately
M|Smal|it|Learning happens continuously
M|Smal|it|Reduced risk per dpl
M|Smal|See|[references/small-batches.md](references/small-batches.md) for implementation patterns.
M|Lean|**Fo|**
